Sourdough Rolls.
Possibly the oldest of
bread recipes dating as
far back as 4000 B.C. It is
made with a sourdough
"starter," a self perpetuat-
ing yeast mixture made
with a combination of
flour, sugar and water.
This bread became iden-
tified in America through
its use by the Alaskan
Sourdoughs, prospectors
who carried sourdough
starters strapped to their
packs so that they could
make bread anytime they
wanted without having
to walk to the nearest
town, usually miles away.
